Geometry of the domain. Globally (left) the domain
is bounded by radial shells which can approach or recede from
each other depending on the gradients in the background veloc-
ity. Points within the domain move in the radial direction due
to the spherically symmetric background flow. The local model
(right) is a rectangular domain where the horizontal coordinates
are equivalent to the latitude/longitude on the sphere and the
vertical direction moves between spherical shells comoving with
the background flow. The aspect ratio of this local box changes
as the distance between the spherical shells varies.
